摘要

第一次的正式讀書會討論，內容主要以Logistic Regression與LDA兩種方法做討論，運用 KaggleEDA後的資料來練習modeling，並做一個簡單的討論。

資料準備

資料的準備部分，我想用做基本的方式來練習模型的建立，另一方面，因為Titanic Dataset的testing data沒有相對應的分類，所以我只用到training dataset來練習。

訓練資料與變數擷取

# EDA後訓練資料
train_ti = read.csv("train_EDA_ti.csv",header = T,stringsAsFactors = TRUE)
# 所需建模變數
var = c("Survived","Title","Sex","Fare","Age","Pclass","FsizeD","SibSp","Embarked","Parch","Child","Mother")
# 選擇變數後的訓練資料
train_ti[,var] -> temp_train
temp_train$Survived = as.factor(temp_train$Survived)

data splitting

  • 以8:2進行分割
  • 試著用caretpackage來建模
# data splitting
library(caret)
set.seed(353)
# 資料分割設定
trainIndex <- createDataPartition(temp_train$Survived, p = .8, 
                                  list = FALSE, 
                                  times = 1)
#head(trainIndex)
# 訓練
temp_tr = temp_train %>% 
  slice(trainIndex)
# 測試
temp_te = temp_train %>% 
  slice(-trainIndex)
temp_tr %>% 
  datatable()
temp_te %>% 
  datatable()

Logistic Regression Model

# model 
fitControl <- trainControl(method = "repeatedcv",
                           number = 10,
                           repeats = 10,
                           ## Estimate class probabilities
                           classProbs = TRUE,
                           ## Evaluate performance using 
                           ## the following function
                           summaryFunction = twoClassSummary)

# 這筆資料有些問題，必須運用因子重新定義名稱才不會有bug！！！
levels(temp_tr$Survived) <- make.names(levels(factor(temp_tr$Survived)))
levels(temp_te$Survived) <- make.names(levels(factor(temp_te$Survived)))
# 
model_lr <- train(Survived ~.,
                       temp_tr,
                       method="glmnet",
                       #tuneLength = 10,
                       metric="ROC",
                       trControl=fitControl)

怪異紀錄

其實用density看出了這兩種分類在分佈上有很明顯的重疊，是不是與類別變數不適合用LDA來做有關，這目前我不知道，但可以很明顯道出他們重疊的滿嚴重的。

# density 觀察
ggplot(lda.pred, aes(x=LD1, fill=Survived)) + geom_density(alpha=0.5)

Using caret to do

# 重新定義模型設定
fitControl <- trainControl(method="repeatedcv",
                            number = 10, # threshold for pca preprocess
                            repeats = 5,
                            classProbs = TRUE,
                            summaryFunction = twoClassSummary)
# LDA get
model_lda <- train(Survived ~.,
                       temp_tr,
                       method="lda",
                       #tuneLength = 10,
                       metric="ROC",
                       preProc = c("center", "scale"),
                       trControl=fitControl)
# 預測
pred_lda <- predict(model_lda,temp_te[,-1])
# confusion matrix
cm_lda <- confusionMatrix(pred_lda, temp_te$Survived, positive = "X1")
cm_lda
